      "content": "thanks. i'll look into valgrind but we're on a very constrained embedded environment so i can't always run full profilers. it's hard because the leak is so slow, it's like it's hiding. can you give me some specific code patterns or common C++ pitfalls i should scan for manually? like specific ways pointers or containers might be holding onto memory unintentionally?",
